value.text: Sand Hills, a painting by German artist Ernst Ludwig Kirchner, handed back to the Fischer family after MoMA recognised that it was stolen by the NazisThe New York Museum of Modern Art (MoMA) has returned a painting stolen by the Nazis to the heirs of its rightful owner, after a decade-long dispute.Ernst Ludwig Kirchner’s vivid yellow, red and black Sand Hills – featuring jagged brush strokes deemed as degenerate by the Nazis – was left behind by Max Fischer when he fled Germany for the US in 1935.
